parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift interlock can cause the vehicle to shift out of park without depressing the brake pedal, leading to unintended movement and potential accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle shifts out of park without depressing the brake pedal
especially when the 4-way flashers are activated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the transmission and loud noise can indicate a serious internal failure, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Loud noise coming from the transmission

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch linkage can cause the transmission to stick in gear, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
The failure of the driveshaft can cause it to fall off, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents, as well as damage to other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping out of gear can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents.
The failure of the automatic locking hubs can cause the steering wheel to jerk or slide on wet pavement, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Automatic locking hubs reengage after using 4WD
causing steering wheel to jerk or slide on wet pavement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission oil line leaks can cause the transmission to fail, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
The failure of the transmission column gear shifter can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
A faulty oxygen sensor can cause the engine to run rich or lean, leading to decreased fuel efficiency, increased emissions, and potential engine damage.
Head gasket failure can cause engine coolant and oil to leak, leading to overheating, engine damage, and potentially causing the engine to fail.
Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
The malfunction of the ABS can cause the front tires to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the front tires lock up when applying the brakes
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brakes fail to function properly

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Overweight Vehicle
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes due to an overweight vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving in hilly terrain.
symptoms: The brakes fail to function properly
the brakes have a burning smell
